		<title>07LOCAL HISTORY</title>
		<content>                                       
 The village cross in Hathern was      
 situated in original centre of village
 and dates back to the fourteenth      
 century.Among reasons given for it    
 being there are that it  was believed 
 to keep away evil and the             
 plague.Hathern used to be called      
 "Wicked Hathern" because villagers did
 not believe in Christianity_was the   
 last village to adopt the religion.The
 local village school was originally a 
 church school, built around 1870 and  
 used for poor children.               
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
